<org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1" xmi:id="-MfaHZYGzr0usn85ZExXG6Q" name="review_results,_29swARETEd-nONyo76otpQ" guid="-MfaHZYGzr0usn85ZExXG6Q" changeDate="2010-04-28T10:15:19.712-0700" changeDescription="Jan 9, 2010: Initial version |" version="7.5.0">
  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Following each review meeting, the results of the meeting should be documented in some form of &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../core.gen.common.extend-ibm/workproducts/review_record_CA816ECE.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;{4047B5B0-5FB7-4960-8A7E-451719D85DFF}&quot;>Review Record&lt;/a>. In addition, change request may be formally recorded&#xD;
    (and eventually assigned to someone to own and drive to resolution).&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    One of the most important, yet surprisingly often neglected, aspects of reviews is the management to resolution of the&#xD;
    follow-up tasks or actions identified during the review. While you can usually assign many of the identified actions&#xD;
    during the course of the review meeting itself, be prepared to reassign tasks as needed to help balance the workload of&#xD;
    team members.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Even if you can review everything you need to in a single meeting, you probably won't get approval of all your&#xD;
    conclusions the first time. Be prepared to carry out subsequent reviews as necessary to help manage the undertaking of&#xD;
    a large number of follow-up tasks.&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
  <sections xmi:id="_MFovcBWoEd-I57lRAWnuXA" name="Prioritize the list of problems" guid="_MFovcBWoEd-I57lRAWnuXA"/>
  <sections xmi:id="_N3MMoBWoEd-I57lRAWnuXA" name="Create defects to track the problems and their resolution" guid="_N3MMoBWoEd-I57lRAWnuXA"/>
  <sections xmi:id="_P9JzkBWoEd-I57lRAWnuXA" name="If additional investigation is required, assign a small team to research the problem (but not to solve it)" guid="_P9JzkBWoEd-I57lRAWnuXA"/>
  <sections xmi:id="_RtESABWoEd-I57lRAWnuXA" name="For problems that can be resolved in the current iteration, assign a person or team to fix the problem" guid="_RtESABWoEd-I57lRAWnuXA"/>
  <sections xmi:id="_TeBSQBWoEd-I57lRAWnuXA" name="Feed the list of unresolved problems into future iteration planning efforts" guid="_TeBSQBWoEd-I57lRAWnuXA"/>
  <purpose>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The purpose of this task is to emphasize conducting the results, otherwise if nothing is done, the review is of little&#xD;
    value.&#xD;
&lt;/p></purpose>
